<p>Basing on <a href="https://docs.jboss.org/hibernate/orm/4.1/manual/en-US/html_single/#performance-fetching-profiles" rel="nofollow">documentation</a>, I appended the fetch-profile inside class. It doesn't validate and I don't know why.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt; &lt;!DOCTYPE hibernate-mapping PUBLIC "-//Hibernate/Hibernate Mapping DTD 3.0//EN" "http://www.hibernate.org/dtd/hibernate-mapping-3.0.dtd"&gt; &lt;hibernate-mapping package="com.mycompany.nncloudrestservice.model"&gt;   &lt;class name="User" table="users"&gt;     &lt;meta attribute="class-description"&gt;         Description under construction     &lt;/meta&gt;     &lt;id name="id" type="int"&gt;         &lt;column name="id_user" not-null="true"/&gt;         &lt;generator class="native"/&gt;     &lt;/id&gt;     &lt;property name="login" column="login" type="string"/&gt;     &lt;property name="email" column="email" type="string"/&gt;     &lt;property name="password" column="password" type="string"/&gt;     &lt;property name="activated" column="activated" type="boolean"/&gt;      &lt;property name="info_to_admin" column="info_to_admin" type="string"/&gt;     &lt;property name="session_id" column="session_id" type="string"/&gt;     &lt;property name="registered" column="registered" type="date"/&gt;     &lt;bag name="networks" cascade="all" table="networks" inverse="true" lazy="true"&gt;         &lt;key column="id_user" not-null="true"/&gt;         &lt;one-to-many class="Network"/&gt;     &lt;/bag&gt;     &lt;fetch-profile name="user-with-networks"&gt;       &lt;fetch association="networks" style="join"/&gt;     &lt;/fetch-profile&gt;     &lt;one-to-one name="performance_settings" cascade="all" class="PerformanceSettings"&gt;&lt;/one-to-one&gt;   &lt;/class&gt; &lt;/hibernate-mapping&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Validation result:</p>  <pre><code>Element type "fetch-profile" must be declared. [23]  Element type "fetch" must be declared. [24]  The content of element type "class" mus